.Dd May 29, 1998
.Dt PTHREAD_ATTR_GETSTACKADDR 3
.Os BSD 4
.Sh NAME
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize ,
.Nm pthread_attr_setstacksize 
.Nd pthread creation stacksize attribute
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <pthread.h>
.Ft int
.Fn pthread_attr_getstacksize "pthread_attr_t *attr" "size_t **stacksize"
.Ft int
.Fn pthread_attr_setstacksize "pthread_attr_t *attr" "size_t *stacksize"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Pp
This interface is defined by
.St -p1003.1c .
.Pp
The 
.Fn pthread_attr_getstacksize
and
.Fn pthread_attr_setstacksize
functions retrieve and establish the stacksize attribute in the 
pthread creation attribute pointed to by
.Fa attr .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Upon successful completion the
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize
and
.Nm pthread_attr_setstacksize
functions both return 0.  A non-zero result indicates
an error occurred.
Upon successful completion the
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize
function returns a copy of the stacksize attribute value in the location
pointed to by
.Fa stacksize .
.Sh ERRORS
The
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize
and
.Nm pthread_attr_setstacksize
functions may fail and return the following error:
.Bl -tag -width Er
.It Bq Er EINVAL
The value of a function argument is invalid.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pthreads 3 ,
.Xr pthread_attr 3 ,
.Xr pthread_create 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize
and
.Nm pthread_attr_setstacksize
functions conform to
.St -p1003.1c .
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm pthread_attr_getstacksize
and
.Nm pthread_attr_setstacksize
functions first appeared in BSD/OS 4.0.
